title.narrative: By 2021, strengthened health sector capacity for integrated MNCH service delivery

description.narrative: The COVID-19 pandemic has revealed gaps in accessing and utilizing essential maternal, newborn, child, adolescent health services, particularly to vulnerable populations. In response, UNICEF supported the prioritization of the community health systems strengthening for primary health care to achieve universal health coverage. The pandemic and its impacts on the economy and on health financing propelled the Ministry of Health and partners to collaborate and work jointly for community based maternal and child health. Innovations and digital technologies were introduced, and high impact interventions were fast tracked, including the introduction of oxygen therapy for pediatrics. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/01/2022
